page.title: 03Ecology, birds and mammals
page.content: Resident birds of the wooded areas are; most tits & thrushes, blackbird, tawny owl, nut hatch, tree creeper and all 3 woodpeckers. In the more open spaces there are; finches, little owl, pied & grey wagtail, skylark & yellowhammer. Rooks, crows, jackdaws jays, house sparrows, robin, dunnock & wren are present. Summer migrants include swallow, house martin, swift, spotted flycatcher, blackcap, chiffchaff, willow & garden warbler. Nightjar & wood warbler are occassionally seen. Winter migrants include redwing & fieldfare with some bramblings. Many gulls also come inland; blackhead, common, herring & greater blackhead. Mammals include deer, foxes, badgers, hedgehogs, grey squirrels,rabbits,moles,shrews, voles & mice. There are some bats, numbers & species currently being researched.
